@startuml
!define ICONS /Users/iworldafric/dev/diagrams/plantuml-stdlib/stdlib/tupadr3
!include ICONS/font-awesome-5/eye.puml
!include ICONS/font-awesome-5/bolt.puml
!include ICONS/font-awesome-5/cog.puml
!include ICONS/font-awesome-5/brain.puml
!include ICONS/font-awesome-5/search.puml
!include ICONS/common.puml

skinparam dpi 150
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #0E6655
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #1ABC9C
skinparam ActivityFontColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityFontSize 13
skinparam ActivityArrowColor #48C9B0
skinparam ActivityArrowFontColor #1C2833
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #1A5276
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #2980B9
skinparam ActivityDiamondFontColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityStartColor #2ECC71
skinparam ActivityEndColor #E74C3C
skinparam shadowing true
skinparam RoundCorner 12
skinparam Padding 8

title Perception Engine — Data Flow

start

:<$eye> **Raw Environment Signals**
FSEvents (file changes), Claude Code hook payloads,
stdout/stderr streams, user messages;

:<$search> **Signal Detection**
Classify signal type: FileChange | ToolOutput | UserInput | Error | Completion.
Extract metadata: path, tool name, exit code, timestamp;

:<$cog> **Structured Parsing**
Normalise to PerceptSchema { type, payload, confidence }.
Validate schema — reject malformed signals.
Apply deduplication window (500ms);

:<$brain> **Prediction Comparison**
Compare against active prediction from Deliberation Engine.
Compute surprise score = |predicted − actual|.
Flag high-surprise events for attention boost;

:<$bolt> **Attention Scoring**
Score each percept: salience × surprise × recency.
Apply budget: keep top-N percepts per cycle.
Route urgent percepts directly to Action layer;

:<$eye> **Structured Percepts**
Emit normalised PerceptStream to Memory Fabric.
Update world-model delta.
Return attention-weighted context to Deliberation Engine;

stop
@enduml
